trans-unit.source: We offer individual developer accounts and company developer accounts in many countries and regions.
trans-unit.target: We offer individual developer accounts and company developer accounts in many countries and regions.

trans-unit.source: We offer two types of developer accounts: individual accounts, and company accounts.
trans-unit.target: We offer two types of developer accounts: individual accounts, and company accounts.

trans-unit.source: Developer accounts are offered in many [countries and regions](#developer-account-and-app-submission-markets).
trans-unit.target: Developer accounts are offered in many [countries and regions](#developer-account-and-app-submission-markets).

trans-unit.source: Either type of account gives you access to publish apps to the Store and to participate in additional Microsoft developer programs.
trans-unit.target: Either type of account gives you access to publish apps to the Store and to participate in additional Microsoft developer programs.

trans-unit.source: **Note** Whether you create an account for a company or an individual, you can associate only one Microsoft account with the developer account.
trans-unit.target: **Note** Whether you create an account for a company or an individual, you can associate only one Microsoft account with the developer account.

trans-unit.source: When signing up for an account, make sure to sign in with the Microsoft account that you want to use for your developer account.
trans-unit.target: When signing up for an account, make sure to sign in with the Microsoft account that you want to use for your developer account.

trans-unit.source: When you [begin the signup process](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=615100) you'll need to choose whether to create an individual account or a company account.
trans-unit.target: When you [begin the signup process](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=615100) you'll need to choose whether to create an individual account or a company account.

trans-unit.source: **Important** You cannot change the account type once you make your selection, so be sure to choose the right type.
trans-unit.target: **Important** You cannot change the account type once you make your selection, so be sure to choose the right type.

trans-unit.source: Here are the essential differences between the two account types.
trans-unit.target: Here are the essential differences between the two account types.

trans-unit.source: Restricted from using certain app capabilities
trans-unit.target: Restricted from using certain app capabilities

trans-unit.source: Costs approximately $19 USD (one-time registration fee; the exact amount varies depending on your country or region)
trans-unit.target: Costs approximately $19 USD (one-time registration fee; the exact amount varies depending on your country or region)

trans-unit.source: Requires verification through Symantec or Dun & Bradstreet
trans-unit.target: Requires verification through Symantec or Dun & Bradstreet

trans-unit.source: Requires that your company is recognized as such in the country or region in which it is located
trans-unit.target: Requires that your company is recognized as such in the country or region in which it is located

trans-unit.source: Costs approximately $99 USD (one-time registration fee; the exact amount varies depending on your country or region)
trans-unit.target: Costs approximately $99 USD (one-time registration fee; the exact amount varies depending on your country or region)

trans-unit.source: **Important** If you decide to create a company account, be sure to review our [guidelines for company accounts](opening-a-developer-account.md#additional-guidelines-for-company-accounts).
trans-unit.target: **Important** If you decide to create a company account, be sure to review our [guidelines for company accounts](opening-a-developer-account.md#additional-guidelines-for-company-accounts).

trans-unit.source: Company accounts are a little more expensive, mostly because we take some additional steps to ensure that you are authorized to represent your company and set up the account.
trans-unit.target: Company accounts are a little more expensive, mostly because we take some additional steps to ensure that you are authorized to represent your company and set up the account.

trans-unit.source: One of the main benefits of having a company account is the ability to submit apps that declare additional [App capability declarations](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/Mt270968).
trans-unit.target: One of the main benefits of having a company account is the ability to submit apps that declare additional [App capability declarations](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/Mt270968).

trans-unit.source: Specifically, you must have a company account in order to publish apps that use the following three capabilities:
trans-unit.target: Specifically, you must have a company account in order to publish apps that use the following three capabilities:

trans-unit.source: **enterpriseAuthentication**—Uses Windows credentials for access to a corporate intranet.
trans-unit.target: **enterpriseAuthentication**—Uses Windows credentials for access to a corporate intranet.

trans-unit.source: This is typically used in line-of-business apps that connect to servers within an enterprise.
trans-unit.target: This is typically used in line-of-business apps that connect to servers within an enterprise.

trans-unit.source: (You don't need this capability for generic communication across the internet.)
trans-unit.target: (You don't need this capability for generic communication across the internet.)

trans-unit.source: **sharedUserCertificates**—Enables an app to access software and hardware certificates, such as certificates stored on a smart card.
trans-unit.target: **sharedUserCertificates**—Enables an app to access software and hardware certificates, such as certificates stored on a smart card.

trans-unit.source: This is typically used for financial or enterprise apps that require a smart card for authentication.
trans-unit.target: This is typically used for financial or enterprise apps that require a smart card for authentication.

trans-unit.source: **documentsLibrary**—Allows programmatic access to the user's Documents, filtered to the file type associations declared in the package manifest.
trans-unit.target: **documentsLibrary**—Allows programmatic access to the user's Documents, filtered to the file type associations declared in the package manifest.

trans-unit.source: (You don't need to declare this capability in order to access a user's Documents with the [file picker](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/Hh465174)).
trans-unit.target: (You don't need to declare this capability in order to access a user's Documents with the [file picker](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/Hh465174)).

trans-unit.source: Note that apps targeting Windows Phone 8.1 or earlier cannot use the documentsLibrary capability.
trans-unit.target: Note that apps targeting Windows Phone 8.1 or earlier cannot use the documentsLibrary capability.

trans-unit.source: **Note** In addition, you must contact support and get approval before you can submit apps that declare the **documentsLibrary** capability.
trans-unit.target: **Note** In addition, you must contact support and get approval before you can submit apps that declare the **documentsLibrary** capability.

trans-unit.source: Having a company account does not guarantee that apps using these capabilities will pass certification.
trans-unit.target: Having a company account does not guarantee that apps using these capabilities will pass certification.

trans-unit.source: These capabilities are intended for very specific scenarios, and most apps shouldn't declare them.
trans-unit.target: These capabilities are intended for very specific scenarios, and most apps shouldn't declare them.

trans-unit.source: For company accounts, we use Symantec or Dun & Bradstreet to verify that you’re authorized to create an account for the company that you’re representing.
trans-unit.target: For company accounts, we use Symantec or Dun & Bradstreet to verify that you’re authorized to create an account for the company that you’re representing.

trans-unit.source: This process can take from a few days to a couple of weeks, and often includes a phone call to your company (so make sure your contact information is up to date when you fill out the registration forms).
trans-unit.target: This process can take from a few days to a couple of weeks, and often includes a phone call to your company (so make sure your contact information is up to date when you fill out the registration forms).

trans-unit.source: You can't submit apps from a company account until it's been verified, but while you're waiting, you can [reserve an app name](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/JJ657967), access your Windows Dev Center dashboard, and continue building and testing your app.
trans-unit.target: You can't submit apps from a company account until it's been verified, but while you're waiting, you can [reserve an app name](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/JJ657967), access your Windows Dev Center dashboard, and continue building and testing your app.

trans-unit.source: You can register for your developer account and submit apps if you live or operate a business in a country or region listed below.
trans-unit.target: You can register for your developer account and submit apps if you live or operate a business in a country or region listed below.

trans-unit.source: **Note** We'll add any applicable taxes and fees to the registration fee when you sign up.
trans-unit.target: **Note** We'll add any applicable taxes and fees to the registration fee when you sign up.

trans-unit.source: Also, when we pay you, your bank might charge a fee to receive the payment.
trans-unit.target: Also, when we pay you, your bank might charge a fee to receive the payment.

trans-unit.source: The **Payout** column describes how we'll pay you the money you earn from your apps.
trans-unit.target: The **Payout** column describes how we'll pay you the money you earn from your apps.

trans-unit.source: You'll be able to choose the [payout account](setting-up-your-payout-account-and-tax-forms.md) into which we'll deposit this money.
trans-unit.target: You'll be able to choose the [payout account](setting-up-your-payout-account-and-tax-forms.md) into which we'll deposit this money.

trans-unit.source: **Note** Some markets do not support paid apps (**payout**).
trans-unit.target: **Note** Some markets do not support paid apps (**payout**).

trans-unit.source: In those markets, only free apps can be submitted.
trans-unit.target: In those markets, only free apps can be submitted.

trans-unit.source: The **PayPal** column indicates whether PayPal is a supported payment method that can be used for your [payout account](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/Bg124529) (and, except where noted, for your developer account registration fee).
trans-unit.target: The **PayPal** column indicates whether PayPal is a supported payment method that can be used for your [payout account](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/Bg124529) (and, except where noted, for your developer account registration fee).
